						               													<description>Chasm Explorers was born in mid 2020 after several months of planning, wanting to bring video game mechanics like Diablo and Ultima Online to a board game. You can also use it as a rule system to build your own adventures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Look carefully, what an unusual sight: a nameless planet with a synchronous orbit around its star, perfectly divided in half, on one side the perennial frost, on the other a glowing desert. At the equator a series of small settlements united by narrow streets to the only immense city, called Pyraqva, dimly illuminated by an eternal dawn. And then there is the Chasm where the Castle once stood, a huge mouth from which emerge unclean screams and creatures that should not exist. After the &amp;quot;Great War&amp;quot; against &amp;quot;The Ancient Evil&amp;quot; and its armies, little remained of that splendid city, but a group of heroes wants to exterminate their enemy once and for all, crossing dangerous paths, corridors of the castle dungeons, immense ravines and enemies of all kinds, up to the last cave at the base of the Chasm, in search of revenge.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME MODES &amp;#10;CO-OP: If a player chooses to face the Dungeon alone he will use 2 characters, the party can have 4 characters in total: therefore 2 players can use one hero  each, or 2 each ... Or 4 players each with their own character. &amp;#10;PVP: You choose a room (Arena) in which to fight, you can use the character from the &amp;quot;Adventure&amp;quot; or create one for this game mode, randomly distributing the abilities on your equipment, and perhaps some enemy  that attacks on sight! You can have a number of players and heroes suited to your needs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
